        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-11T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-11T23:00:00-05:00" n="677" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/9–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-12T13:00:00+09:00">September 12, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 1—10:21 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>144. At conference with Soviet Consul General, I unable learn if any telegrams
                    yet sent direct Moscow (reContels 127, August 28 and 131, August 30).</p>
                <p>I therefore informed him from September 14 I addressing all telegrams only to
                    Moscow Embassy and assume they sent there direct. I will send to Vladivostok
                    only telegrams for that post. I said I ask Embassy acknowledge receipt each
                    telegram (via Shanghai).</p>
                <p>I handicapped by no information actual date Vladivostok to close.</p>
                <p>When it closes I shall send daily telegram, even if only dummy, to Moscow Embassy
                    until certain new route satisfactory.</p>
                <p>Sent Department. Department pass Moscow 41, Nanking 50, Shanghai 80.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
